Theres loads to do in Worms Ultimate Mayhem and veteran Wormers may wish to jump straight into the endless amount of options and content. But for rookies, heres a quick guide./*NL*/ /*NL*/The game is turn-based, and during your turn, you can move a worm, unleash a Utility or Weapon, or do both./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/Once your turn is over it is then your opponents chance (CPU or player controlled) to do the same./*NL*/ /*NL*/If you have the Worm Select Utility, you can change which worm you use for that turn, otherwise it will simply be the next worm in order./*NL*/ /*NL*/Your turn is over once your worm has fired a weapon, taken damage from either an environmental hazard or falling too far, or your turn time runs out./*NL*/ /*NL*/In most situations once a worm has fired a weapon, they enter Retreat Time. This is a small window of time in which they can still be moved before the turn is over, and this is used to... err... retreat./*NL*/ /*NL*/Once a players turn has ended, the game enters Hot Seat Time./*NL*/This is a small pause between turns to allow the controller to be passed to the next player. /*NL*/ /*NL*/Hot Seat Time can be cancelled at any time by simply using any of the controls./*NL*/ /*NL*/Battles can consist of up to 4 teams of worms taking it in turns to shoot at each other until the selected win/*NL*/ /*NL*/condition for that game has been met (which is usually that only one team of worms remains). Once the win condition is met, the game is over!

This is the heart of single player worming where youll play through the story of the game./*NL*/ /*NL*/Complete the four available missions in any order within a theme to unlock the final Boss mission./*NL*/ /*NL*/Complete this to move on to the next theme and the next set of 4 missions./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/By completing themes in the Story mode you also unlock Campaign Missions. These are unlocked in groups of seven and can be completed in any order./*NL*/ /*NL*/You get the first seven for free so why not see what they are like you might get a surprise!

Play friends, the CPU or both in an all-out, fully-customisable skirmish. Choose a game type from the five available:/*NL*/ /*NL*/ - Deathmatch is the classic multiplayer mode in which the last team standing is declared the winner./*NL*/ /*NL*/ - Homelands sees each team start with control of a fort that can be used tactically during the battle. The last team standing wins/*NL*/ - Destruction is a race to destroy the enemys base. The coloured bars show the remaining land for each player./*NL*/ /*NL*/ - Statue Defend tasks players with destroying their enemies statues whilst trying to defend their own. The last team with a statue wins./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ - Survivor limits teams to only one worm at a time with which to defeat the enemy. The death of that worm spawns in another one until that team has none left to spawn./*NL*/ /*NL*/With a game mode selected, you can then edit the team options by selecting a team from the left hand side of the screen. You can alter many aspects of each team; from health to alliance./*NL*/ /*NL*/You can also change the battlefield by selecting the map preview, then selecting one of the many maps available. /*NL*/ /*NL*/Alternatively, let the game randomly generate one for you, set a Game Style or just let Wormpot do the work./*NL*/ /*NL*/When youre happy with the game settings, you can jump into battle./*NL*/ /*NL*/Make sure you fully explore the Versus options as youll discover a game that has many, many possibilities!

Each Challenge tests your skills in a different aspect of the game. You can also test your skills in the Deathmatch Challenges./*NL*/ /*NL*/Either way, there are a ton of Challenges to sink your teeth into!

This mode works much the same as the Quick Match option in the Local Game settings./*NL*/ /*NL*/It searches for any game type and any number of players on any map./*NL*/ /*NL*/ This is a Player Match so there is nothing at stake other than pride.

Challenge people online for points!/*NL*/ /*NL*/You can select the type of game you wish to play but not the map./*NL*/ /*NL*/Battle up to three other players at the same time using a special Ranked Match Game Style on randomly selected maps./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/Winning matches earns you points and propels you up the Leaderboards, but failing to win could see you slide down./*NL*/ /*NL*/Are you up to the challenge of competitive play?

This mode allows you to search the entire world for a game that suits your preferences. Simply select a team and set out your search parameters./*NL*/ /*NL*/Search for a specific Game Type, Game Style, or Number of Players, or alternatively, leave the search parameters open to increase your chances of finding a game./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/This is a Player Match so there are no points at stake, and if theres room in the lobby, you can invite a friend to join in the fun.

Cant find a Custom Match that floats your boat? Fear not! Just create the perfect match, set every aspect of the game as the host, then wait for other players to join your lobby./*NL*/ /*NL*/You have all the same options found offline, from team select to Game Style and even what map (including randomly generated or saved maps) the battles take place on./*NL*/ /*NL*/As youre the host you can even set private slots./*NL*/ /*NL*/Only people you invite can join in a private slot, so have an entirely private game with friends, or set a few slots as private ones and you and your friends can gang up on poor unsuspecting people that stumble into your lobby./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/This is a Player Match so no points are up for grabs, but thats fine since you have more options to play with than Dr. O. In this mode, all the games you play are worth points. These points make up your Ranked Points (RP)./*NL*/ /*NL*/You have a different set of Ranked Points for each game type you can play./*NL*/ /*NL*/You gain or lose more Ranked Points based on both the skill of the players you are playing against and how well you do during the game./*NL*/ /*NL*/The exact science behind how it works is our little secret... /*NL*/ /*NL*/However, its safe to say that killing enemy worms and winning games (or at least placing as high as you can) will improve your score, so try and inflict as much damage as you can whilst minimising your own teams losses./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/As you gain Ranked Points across all the different game types, theyre added together to give you a Player Points (PP) score./*NL*/ /*NL*/Your Player Points are an indication of your overall ability at the game, so try to earn points in every game type and claim the top spot!

Weve been kind enough to get you started with a few preset teams, however at some point youre going to want to create your own squad of worm avengers, so heres some hints./*NL*/ /*NL*/Firstly, choose whether the team you create will be a Human or CPU-controlled team (including how good the CPU will be), then jump in and make that team distinctive./*NL*/ /*NL*/Give the worms names and choose what they will say from a wide range of hilarious options./*NL*/ /*NL*/Try out the different soundbanks with the test option and find one that makes you chuckle./*NL*/ /*NL*/Customise your teams hands, eyes and facial features you can make them look cool, scary or silly./*NL*/ /*NL*/Each option you try appears on the worm, so you can see just what your creation will look like. Some options however prevent others from being used, so experiment and try thing out./*NL*/ /*NL*/Lastly, give your team a flag, team weapon and gravestone, then youre done! Doesnt seem like there are enough items to use?/*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/Well, go purchase some new ones from the Items Shop./*NL*/ /*NL*/Once youre done, remember you can always come back and edit a team with Edit Team or ditch them with Delete Team.

So youve created a team, well thats great! But every team needs its own signature weapon... right?/*NL*/ /*NL*/This screen allows you to create your very own super team weapon./*NL*/ /*NL*/Use the options on the right hand side of the screen to set your weapons properties, choose what the contraption looks like, what it fires, whether its explosive, poisonous or homing./*NL*/However nothing in this world is free dont think you can just make a weapon of Wormageddon proportions!/*NL*/ /*NL*/Keep an eye on the gauge in the bottom left corner of the screen. If your weapons too powerful youll overload it and any weapon in the red area on the gauge cant be saved or used./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/Remember, if you make a pile of scrap metal you can always tweak it with Edit Weapon or if its a lost cause you can simply delete it.
Your worms can be made to crawl around the environments using the /*Button.Movement*/ buttons./*NL*/Got all that? Good. Now hop to it!

Even though the game offers many Game Styles to choose from (with many more to unlock), you can also create your own customized Game Styles by changing every aspect of the game, from the weapons allowed to how powerful the wind is./*NL*/ /*NL*/Explore the Game Style Builder to create customized experiences for you and your friends to play offline or online./*NL*/Once saved, dont forget you can always edit or delete them with Edit Game Style and Delete Game Style.

You earn coins by playing the game, completing missions, completing challenges and beating best times./*NL*/ /*NL*/Spend your coins in the Items Shop on new ways to customise your worm, new multiplayer maps, new weapons and plenty more... theres more than 40 items to be bought!

Change the control and sound options here to suit your own personal preferences or simply sit back and marvel at the amazing talent that has brought you this game by watching the credits./*NL*/ /*NL*/You never know what you might discover by doing this.

As well as the plethora of maps you have available to play, you can also choose to play on a randomly-generated map, giving you an almost infinite amount of maps to play on./*NL*/ /*NL*/If you dont like the look of the map generated in the preview simply highlight the preview window and press /*FETXT.Control.Blimp*/ to generate another one./*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/Randomly-generated maps can also be saved. Once in a game, simply bring up the pause menu with the /*FETXT.Control.Pause*/ key and select the Save Level option. Want to know something cool? Thought so!/*NL*/ /*NL*/When playing in Network Play, if the map you are playing on is a randomly-generated one and you like it, you can save it, even if it wasnt generated by yourself... share the wealth!

Before you begin a game, you must first select a Game Style./*NL*/ /*NL*/Game Styles affect the way the game plays as well as defining various things within a game such as:/*NL*/ /*NL*/ - What Weapons or Utilities teams start with./*NL*/ /*N*/ - How long turn times and game time are./*NL*/ - What Sudden Death option is used at the end of the game./*NL*/    - How effective assisted shot is./*NL*/   - How strong the Wind is./*NL*/   - Other options including how often      Crates drop and how many/*NL*/   environmental hazards there are./*NL*/ /*NL*/There are some predefined Game Styles to get you started with, and more that can be unlocked, but if you wish, you can create your own and save them.

Wormpot is a way of generating random game modifiers that change the Game Style you are using./*NL*/ /*NL*/You can spin all the reels with the lever or nudge the reels individually. Each reel represents an element of gameplay that will be altered./*NL*/ /*NL*/By pressing /*FETXT.Control.MenuSelect*/ you can bring up information about what each reel will do.

Each of your worms has a set starting amount of health. During a worms turn, its health is shown in the top right corner of the screen. It appears just under the currently selected Weapon and is displayed as a number. /*NL*/  /*NL*/Falling too far, enemy attacks, mishandling explosives and friendly fire all remove health points from your worm. When all your worms health points are gone, so is its life./*NL*/If a worm falls into water regardless of the amount of health points they have remaining, they die./*NL*/ /*NL*/Health can be replenished by collecting Health Crates./*NL*/ /*NL*/If you combine the total health points of all your worms, you get your team status. /*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/The team status bar appears at the bottom of the screen between turns and when a player is speaking using a Mic. It shows which team is winning, and which team(s) are losing. /*NL*/ /*NL*/A smaller team status bar can be found just below the health point of your worm. Its a good idea to keep an eye on this as once this bar is empty, you and your team are history!

When the round time reaches zero, the game enters Sudden Death (unless playing Destruction or Statue Defend Game Styles). /*NL*/ /*NL*/When Sudden Death starts, the rules set within the Game Style come into play ensuring that the game concludes quickly. Sudden Death can be any of the following/*NL*/ /*NL*/ /*NL*/ - All remaining worms have their health reduced to 1 health point./*NL*/ /*NL*/ - The water level rises by a set amount at the end of each turn./*NL*/ /*NL*/ - The game is counted as a draw regardless of who is in the lead.

This isn't right! A collection of freeloading extraterrestrials have connected up to the main grid and are sapping energy like there's no tomorrow. 
 
They're running up a heinous bill and need to be stopped. Disconnect the thieving suckers permanently, if you know what I mean.

What's this? Not content with your veg, now he wants your fruit! The greedy Farmer Boggy Pete's tricked a group of industrious ants into delivering your precious cherries right up to his door step. What a rude worm! Thankfully fruit isn't the only thing ants collect and a handy little package on top of the ant hill should help curtail his villainous activities. You must collect the crate and stop him before he stops you.

Land ahoy! Whilst sailing the seven seas we happened upon this small cluster of islands. A quick search of the area revealed a treasure chest sat atop a lofty perch and closely guarded by a scurvy old sea dog.  Unfortunately we came ill-prepared and need help in figuring out a way to reach this booty. You'll just have to use your head!

Up, up and away! 
Our reconnaissance patrol has been ambushed. Evil enemy worms are closing in on our balloon with the intent of bursting our bubble. Take heart though, a direct hit to their aircraft will cause them to explode. Destroy the enemy and turn this situation around... it sounds simple but expect the unexpected!

Fe fi fo fum, I smell the blood of a fat pink worm.... Yes! We've stolen the golden egg. All that is left is to escape back down the stalk to ground level. The problem is we've left plenty of evidence and this needs to be cleared up on the way down before the giant wakes up. Use your Parachute to get the worms down to the base of the beanstalk and collect all 15 of the targets on the way down and get each worm into the boat before the end of it's turn. You have 3 turns to do so and don't lose any worms. Failure will result in fried worm sandwiches all round, Gulp!

Use your Parachute to get the worms down to the base of the beanstalk and collect all 15 of the targets on the way down. Failure will result in fried worm sandwiches all round, Gulp!

It's a well known taboo that worms and humans just don't mix. So it is with regret that I must inform you that a group of upstart anarchists have broken this sacred rule and entered the abode of Homo Sapiens. If they are discovered then our reputation could be irrevocably damaged, forever blighted with the label "vermin". We cannot allow this to happen. Eliminate the house invaders!

We're not usually ones to get embroiled in other people's battles but this is one we simply cannot ignore! The peaceful "Planet of the Spotless Robots" is being inundated with dirty, soiled crates... and something has to be done about it! That's why we're sending you in, the "Clean-up King", to deal with this mess. Get those crates collected and deal with the offending worms. Good luck!

Tonight is All Hallow's Eve and the Undead have arisen once more to cause mischief and mayhem. Before the night's out those pesky perpendicular corpses must be sent back to their worm-infested graves. Use anything and everything available to make light work of the task... kill them all, and you might just live to see another dawn.

Oh Man, we've been cooped up... quite literally! We've been stripped of our weapons and locked in the chicken coop! Luckily we thought this might happen and posted some weapons to this address. Escape the coop, collect the weapons from the mailbox, then teach the enemy a lesson... Be warned, though the enemy is distracted it's only a matter of time before they'll realise you've escaped.

Our Colonel has been working way too hard recently and he's so stressed that he can't even sleep at night!  We've brought him to this peaceful farm in the hope he can get some rest. Seeing that you're already here you might as well try to help! Explore the farm carefully and see if you can find a way to send him to sleep.

What's this? Farmer Boggy Pete's farm-hands have got their mucky mitts on our secret miracle grow formula, stored on a nearby island and conveniently packaged in a rather tidy crate. The greedy farmer intends to drive us out of business with his oversized meat and veg. It's up to you to bend his cauliflower ear and foil his evil plan... It may sound corny but grow above the task and collect that crate.

Oh dear! Our hero has managed to land himself right in the middle of a bloody space gang battle, and boy does he need your help! Take control of The Crocketeer and keep him out of trouble long enough for our rescue ship to collect him! You may find some crates to help, while detonating the mines on the landscape might allow opportunties to use the prod... remember, the less enemies there are, the higher your chances of survival!

The farmer isn't happy. Not only do mysterious patterns keep appearing in his crop field, but now bullies from another universe turn up and start causing trouble! Well it's just not on!  
Collect the weaponry and deal with the baddies. Good luck!

Oh dear! Some nasty thieves have stolen all our local miller's quality goods. It's up to you to recover them all and catch the little rascals, so it's nose to the grindstone and after them. If you catch them make sure they get it right in the kernels, that should make their eyes water! Collect all three health crates behind the windmill and destroy the enemy. Losing just one health crate will end the mission in failure.

This is it! The beach assault is on! Eliminate the enemy before the main force lands. Secure the beach and head inland: while the enemy has the high ground they have the advantage... 
Look out for air supplies, and whatever you do, get off the beach: failure to do so will result in a bloodbath!

"This is red one I've been hit ... she's gonna blow."
"Roger that Red One, bail out, bail out ..."
"Roger Mother Goose. Ahhh! I see the Bandit that shot me, permission to descend and destroy. Over."
"Permission granted Red One happy hunting. Over."

After a fun day at the fair you can't just slink away without paying! These disgruntled carnival folk are a shrewd breed, and don't take kindly to freeloaders! The cost of each attraction is one Land Mine. Collect the crates and drop the payment at each individual ticket booth. The ride owners aren't going to let you go until they've been paid!

Mission complete.. Now on to the next one!

This graveyard is home to some very wealthy corpses buried along with their valuables. We've decided it's time these treasures were unearthed for all to share, and you're just the worm for the task!  Beware mind, only four of the graves hide treasure while the others spell certain doom!

Bully boys have cornered a cowardly scaredy-cat atop the Helter Skelter! Be a pal and help this kid out by collecting the weaponry scattered about the islands and dispatching of the bad guys. You must hurry though: the enemy will soon have access to Air Strikes... if they kill the worm on top of the helter skelter it'll be mission over!

An ancient evil has awakened at the mansion on "Damnation Hill"! The Prince of Darkness and his legions of Undead are growing in power and must be stopped. Van Wormsing and his team are charged with destroying this threat, and with your ability, they should prove more than a match for the powers of darkness. Without their leader the Undead will die, but only Van Wormsing can destroy the Dark Lord... so keep him alive or evil will rule the world!

This island was once a popular vacation destination but now it's littered with dangerous explosive mines. The vacation season is about to start and we need you to make the island safe once more before somebody gets hurt! You have eight minutes; if that time expires and the island is still classed as hazardous we'll be destroying it completely just to ensure no hapless sun-seekers get hurt. They'd like to be golden brown, not charred remains!

The infamous pirate Pink Beard has been terrifying the open seas for too long. Finally, the powers that be have decided the cad and his henchmen have over stepped the mark and wish this threat was no longer an issue. However, it seems that some nautical nitwit has dispatched our heroes to the wrong location... What are we to do? I know! If you can't get to the target, perhaps clever use of an old skimming technique would prove bountiful in this situation.

Is nothing beyond that callous worm? The Sheep-rustling Farmer Boggy Pete has stolen an entire flock of our beloved Sheep and is planning on dropping them into the icy water. He's prepared a large hole in the ice, not far from Christmas Mountain - this could be one dip from which they'll never surface. Find a way of stopping the executions!

Disaster Mate! We've been ambushed by Boggy Pete and his henchmen. And worse... our operation faces a wash-out as his henchmen have turned the tap on. Take care of those henchmen while making your way upwards to avoid the water. I'm sure you can find one or two goodies to help on the way. Water-way to go!

Working on a movie set behind the scenes is not as glamorous as a lead role, yet still as important! Unfortunately, our movie director has high blood pressure, and if you don't follow his directions he could end up blowing his top. The loss of the director would ruin the movie, so I think you had better do as he says, don't you?

We have an emergency on our hands! One of our top Wormonaut's has found himself in a real sticky situation and needs to get a move on if he is to survive! Climb to the shuttle before the water overtakes you! HURRY UP, AND DON'T LOOK DOWN!

DISASTER! The camera crew have gone berserk and need dealing with before they wreck the whole place! Use any weaponry you have at hand and get rid of this mob before it gets out of hand. Cameras ready, prepare to flash!

At last we've got a copy of "Worms 3D", but before we managed to even get a play, a pesky prankster has gone and maliciously broken our monitor!  Take a look at the monitor repair book on the desk and try to rewire it. But be sure to check your wiring before you hit the power switch... you wouldn't want a blow-out now would you?

The Age of Ragnarok is at hand and to be honest it's lousy timing. While the Gods nap, we've been overrun by Pagan worms... You must save us! However, we are but simple folk and can only offer a mere Jet Pack to aid you in your quest. Luckily, the weapons of the Gods have been scattered about Yggdrasil, the tree of life. Collect them and send the those Pagans back to the murky depths from whence they came.
Okay chaps, your mission is quite simple really. Storm the enemy installation, take the key locations and hold them for 5 turns. Remember hold until relieved. Hold until relieved ... echo, echo.

Our hero's vacation didn't quite go to plan; the tour of the dock ran into some stormy weather and ended up losing some of the tourists in the drink. Fortunately our hero ended up being washed onto the coast of the tiny "Worms Island"... do your best to help him create enough ruckus in order to alert the Coast Guard of his whereabouts so he can be rescued!

Hurry! The Admiral's personal supply of grog is in danger of being lost! Our ship has been blown off course and is now in the clutches of colossal sea monsters! You must use your Jet Pack skills and collect seven of the crates before the time runs out and the monsters gulp down everything. But be warned, the attack has made the barrels under the grog highly volatile... they could explode at the slightest knock! Blow up more than three and you'll find yourself in deep water!

Vandals are trespassing on school property, intent on a course of mid-term madness. Well, I think it's high time we taught them a bit about corporal punishment... none of this softly, softly community service or detention nonsense. Make this their hardest lesson yet! Punish the vandals!

Avast ye matey! 
 
Look out, Pink Beards about. The wet whoopsie has attacked his majesty's fleet and plundered our most powerful weapon ... the Concrete Donkey. He's taken it back to his lair at Barnacle Bay... a haven for pirates and privateers alike. Your task is clear: recover our Donkey and pummel the plundering pirates!

From the cold recesses of space they came, without warning they stormed our system and one by one we lost contact, first our outpost space station, then the planet! But the enemy didn't figure on me. This is my story..... strapped to my Jet Pack I must collect crates and rearm. I know I must proceed with caution and can ill-afford to engage in close combat with this most callous invader.

Ooh I say. Look what's reared its ugly head! An evil wizard has summoned a mighty monster from below the waves, and it's up to you, good Sir Worm, to slay the clever conjurer before he unleashes the beast. Take heed this warning though...use any shelter you can to avoid the wizard's gaze... he may have an evil trick or two hidden up that wizard's sleeve.

Washed up on the shores of the infamous pirate haven Skally Island you have but three simple objectives: defeat the enemy pirates, rescue our gracious Captain still stranded on our sorry ship's wreckage, and finally steal the pirate ship anchored in the lagoon. It's either that or picking the weevils out of biscuits, the choice is yours!

These trees have been here for hundreds of years, and we aren't going to let vandals just chop them down!  Intimidated villagers cower inside their huts whilst two of the vandals patrol outside.  Your mission is to take care of these vandals while being careful not to harm the villagers in the process. Tread lightly, and try to stay out of sight!

Welcome to damnation! 
 

On Earth your wicked life has ended and you have been brought before me so that I may pass judgement. What's this you say, you weren't wicked? I must see proof of this! Move through my dominion and reach the prize I keep before me and I will graciously return you your life... But beware the vortex below: that way lies eternal anguish and tortured souls!
